result.name: Champak Resturant by ATUM

reviews.text: Food are highly instragramble. Food is decently nice for lunch sets. Be warned that the portions are pretty small for a grown adult man but flavours are pretty well balanced.
Highly recommendable restaurant. Price is a bit expensive but food is really tasty. Tried twice and feeling satisfied each time.

I go to the forest at Mong Kok a lot because I love to buy vegan and organic stuffs at the store beside Champak restaurant. I decided to try their lunch set and it was really good. The price isn't too expensive ranging from 50-90 HKD with drinks included. It's more of a modern style Southeast Asian food and the  flavor profile is excellent. I really like both the taste of the food and the presentation as well. Another plus point is their beautiful interior, really loving the nice touch all the plants give to the restaurant. I will definitely recommend people to give this place a try.

reviews.author_name: l X l X k X a X
reviews.text: Some staffs were nice! Most of the foods were pretty cool down whiling serving, really disappointed! Tiny dinning table!
food was decent, lacks a bit of service

result.adr_address: 香港旺角奶路臣街17號
result.name: 青花

reviews.text: 味道尚算不錯，只是晚飯限時90分，不能悠閒地用餐
是新fushion的泰菜，但菜式不是很出色，裝修有特色
態度超級差，本來朋友book咗5:30pm2位，但我放工遲了，要我朋友企在外面等我15mins, 而且入面桌全部空，還要我5:45pm不到冇得入座，垃圾餐廳，以後不來

去波鞋街買完波鞋食好西…
波鞋街附近開左個新商場The Forest，原來裡面都有唔少新餐廳，早兩日買完波鞋就去左其中一間泰國餐廳，裝潢似一個小森林，俾人一種好舒適悠閒既感覺，餐廳外面仲有露天座位，遲啲天氣無咁熱一定要喺出面感受下小清新~
-
叫左 二人套餐  HKD$498
☆ 鹹蛋黃青木瓜沙律
☆ 大蝦冬蔭公（小）
☆ 天多尼烤雞 · 斑蘭青咖哩
☆ 金不換卜卜蜆
☆ 香草蒜蓉包
☆ 泰式肥豆兒醬炒芥蘭
☆ 泰象青檸梳打 2 杯
-
冬蔭公係小份，但份量係大份😅 味道幾啱香港人口味，酸味較重含微辣，不錯的。天多尼烤雞幾嫩滑，青咖哩唔係我杯茶，但友人話微微滲出香辣，亦食到有斑蘭味。卜卜蜆用上金不換醬汁製成，幾惹味🤤 每隻蜆都大隻肥厚漲卜卜，食到啖啖肉👍 蒜蓉包熱辣辣，外脆內軟。肥豆兒醬原來係麵豉醬，攞嚟炒芥蘭幾新穎特別😙 不得不提既泰象梳打水永遠都咁好飲，平時唔飲有氣飲品既我都成杯飲哂😊😋
-
總括而言，菜式獨特，口味fusion，上碟夠精緻，份量極多，性價比頗高，大熱天時食下啲新鮮開胃泰菜都係一個唔錯既選擇👍
Food are highly instragramble. Food is decently nice for lunch sets. Be warned that the portions are pretty small for a grown adult man but flavours are pretty well balanced.

result.adr_address: 17 Nelson St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 17 Nelson St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: The FOREST

reviews.text:
lovely Shopping mall in Mong Kok. Approximately 300m from the train station

 you will find on the main sports and sports related outlets plus s variety of restaurants 
building has numerous vertical gardens which creates an outdoor feeling.  ample public spaces, seating areas areas in this multi levels mall. there are also a number of free phone charging stations.  restrooms are extremely clean. 

outlets in the mall are  logically spread out and directional signs legible displayed to assist in the navigation of the mall
a different feel to your usual mall. an easy upscale place.

Nice place to sit and have a snack. The Forest is themed after nature and aims to give you a relaxing experience in the urban concrete jungle. Sadly all the flowers and greens that decorate the place are made from plastic. The stuff that's not really good for forests... Keeping that amount of plants healthy in this environment would be impossible of course but being surrounded by plastic plants is a bit disturbing. The food and drinks are ok an priced at the higher end. Definitely a nice experience
Stylish & model mall at Mongkok, not much choice of shops though. But they have several restaurant there worth trying.
Impressive retail space with an environmental twist filled with greenery and shops with a sustainability angle. Lovely little rooftop garden on 3rd floor.
There are many shop assistants waiting to serve you which made me afraid because I just want to take a look instead of buying anything. Not good for window shopping.

result.name: The FOREST

reviews.text: 這是比较新的商场。在里面的商店公司，佈置擺設都很時尚美观，商品种类繁多，琳琅满目，有波鞋，运动服装和饮食店……等，是購物的好地方。(沒有相片)！
多鞋店，餐廳，空間大，行吓幾好。
旺角一流的大型商場 產品應有盡有 多間著名食肆 交通方便
